article.headline: Delaware 57, William & Mary 52 (OT)
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Rulon Washington scored 16 points and Harding Nana added 12 and 11 rebounds Wednesday night, leading Delaware past William & Mary 57-52 in overtime. The Blue Hens (8-17, 4-12 Colonial Athletic Association) outscored the Tribe 7-2 in the extra period, holding William & Mary without a point for the final 4:10. The Tribe (8-16, 3-12) also didn't score in the final 4:56 of regulation after taking a 50-44 lead, allowing Delaware to overcome a six-point deficit. Sam McMahon tied the game by sinking a pair of free throws with 1:27 left in regulation. Nathan Mann led the Tribe, which shot just 31 percent, with 14 points.
